HireFirst | Release Note & Updates | April 2, 2026 @channel

1. Auto Enrich — Apollo.io Integration
With Auto Enrich, recruiters can now fill in missing profile details with a single click — powered by Apollo's 275M+ contact database.
Available now: Candidates section → open any profile → Auto Enrich

2. Instant Interview — Quick Job Creation
You can now create a new job role on the fly directly inside the Instant Interview flow — no need to set up a job in advance.
Available now: Interviews → Instant Interview

3. Branding Update — RIL Portal
The "Orion" name and logo have been replaced with "HireFirst" across the RIL-facing portal. This applies to the logo, page title, and all visible entry points for the RIL team. The Fynd-internal instance is not affected.

4. RIL Environments — Now Live
Both Production and SIT environments are set up and accessible on the RIL domain:
Production — https://hiring.ril.com
SIT — https://hiring-ril.sit.fyndx1.de/

5. SAP Integration — Connectivity Verified 
SAP connectivity is established and verified. We are currently working through a few SAP proprietary library issues to complete the sync of all OM data.
Core connection is stable, resolution on the library side is in progress and an update will follow once full OM data sync is confirmed.


1. Candidate Blocklist
You can now blocklist a candidate directly from Settings, preventing them from being assigned to any job across the platform while keeping their profile searchable for reference.
Available now: Settings → Block List

